def: Treasonable. Shak.The treasonous book of the Court of King James. Pepys.
One who is six feet tall. [Colloq. U.S.]
Shifting the sword from one side of an adversary's sword to theother.
To make liberal; to free from narrow views or prejudices.To open and to liberalize the mind. Burke.
Changed into a hectocotylus; having a hectocotylis.

To treat or test, as a liquid, with a solution of mercuriciodide in potassium iodide and potassium hydroxide, which is calledNessler's solution or Nessler's test, and is used to detect thepresence of ammonia.
To create at the same time.If God did concreate grace with Adam. Jer. Taylor.
The ace of clubs in qua Pope.
